President Obama spoke with Doctors Without Borders International President Dr. Joanne Liu to apologize and express condolences for the staff and patients who were killed and injured in a U.S. military airstrike on an MSF field hospital in Kunduz, Afghanistan. The President expressed regret and offered his thoughts and prayers to the victims and their families. He assured Dr. Liu that the ongoing Department of Defense investigation would provide a transparent and thorough account of the incident and pledged full cooperation with joint investigations being conducted with NATO and the Afghan Government.